If I understand correctly, currently there's no way to use worker_threads workers when using the o1js library, correct? I was trying to parallelize some of my proof generation with worker_threads, but it seems like even trying to use Field from o1js throws an error in this simple code that I wrote while debugging:

```ts
import { Worker, isMainThread, parentPort, workerData } from 'worker_threads';
import { Field } from 'o1js';

if (isMainThread) {
  const valuesToSquare = [1, 2, 3]; 

  const handleMessage = (result: string) => {
    console.log(result);
  };

  const workerPromises: any = [];

  valuesToSquare.forEach((value) => {
    const worker = new Worker('./build/worker_tests.js', {
      workerData: value,
    });

    const workerPromise = new Promise((resolve) => {
      worker.on('message', (result) => {
        handleMessage(result);
        resolve(result);
      });
    });

    workerPromises.push(workerPromise);
  });

  await Promise.all(workerPromises);

} else {
  const field = Field(workerData);
  parentPort?.postMessage(field.toString());
}
```

It looks like BullMQ plays nicely with `o1js`. This version of my original code using `bullmq` instead of `worker_threads` seems to do what I intended:

```ts
import { Queue, Worker, QueueEvents } from 'bullmq';
import { Field } from 'o1js';

const myQueue = new Queue('foo', { connection: {
    host: '127.0.0.1',
    port: 6379
}});

const queueEvents = new QueueEvents('foo', { connection: {
    host: '127.0.0.1',
    port: 6379
}});

const values = [1,2,3];
const jobsPromises = [];

for (const value of values) {
    const job = await myQueue.add(`job${value}`, { value: value });
    jobsPromises.push(job.waitUntilFinished(queueEvents));

    const worker = new Worker('foo', async job => {
        const field = Field(job.data.value);
        return field.toString();
        }, {
        connection: {
                host: '127.0.0.1',
                port: 6379
            }
        }
    );
};

queueEvents.on('completed', job => {
    console.log(`${job.jobId} has completed and returned ${job.returnvalue}`);
});

await Promise.all(jobsPromises);
```
